<TITLE> National education policy 'within a week' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 30 (bdnews24.com)The national education policy will be completed within a weeknNational professor Kabir Chowdhury said on Tuesday. "We are basing the new education policy based on the four themes of the 1972 Constitution. The draft will be ready by next week," said Chowdhury, chairman of the committee that has been assigned to formulate the policy. Chowdhury was speaking at a seminar on 'Education policy in light of the Liberation War,' arranged by Communist Party of Bangladesh. The new Awami League government, coming to power in January this year, decided to base its education plans mainly on the past Kudrat-e-Khuda education commission's recommendations. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid said no full-fledged commission will be formed again, but the new policy would be a modified and modernised version of previous AL education plans for fast formulation and implementation. He also mentioned that madrasah students would receive "modern lessons" along with religious lessons under the new policy. Nahid announced the formulation committee on Apr 8. It was asked to report within three months from its first sitting so that the implementation of the policy could start this year. The committee had its first sitting on Mar 3. bd
